  "title": "Sales & Shipping Executive/Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description / Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare and verify shipping documents (e.g., invoices, packing lists, Certificates of Origin, Bill of Lading, Insurance).</li><li>Ensure adherence to international trade regulations and Incoterms, beyond basic customs compliance.</li><li>Coordinate legalization or validation of documents when required.</li><li>Negotiate freight rates with carriers and forwarders to optimize costs.</li><li>Arrange bookings with shipping lines, freight forwarders, or courier services.</li><li>Planning and scheduling shipments for cost efficiency and timely delivery.</li><li>Negotiate freight rates with carriers and forwarders to optimize costs.</li><li>Track and monitor shipment schedules to ensure timely delivery.</li><li>Communicate with distributors, customers, and internal teams regarding shipment status.</li><li>Handle shipment delays, discrepancies, or documentation issues.</li><li>Liaise with carriers and customs for problem-solving.</li><li>Manage claims for lost/damaged goods and resolve customs clearance issues.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualification and Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>'O' Levels, Diploma and above or related field.</li><li>Minimum 3 years of experience in shipping knowledge.</li><li>Strong organizational and coordination skills with attention to detail.</li><li>Able to work independently and communicate effectively across teams.</li></ul>",
